# SSH Enumeration Lab

## Objective

Learn how to enumerate an SSH service running on Metasploitable 2 using Nmap.

## Target

- Machine: Metasploitable 2
- IP Address: 192.168.1.15

## Commands Used

```bash
nmap -sV -p 22 192.168.1.15

nmap -sV --version-all -p 22 192.168.1.15

nmap --script ssh2-enum-algos -p 22 192.168.1.15

nmap --script ssh-hostkey -p 22 192.168.1.15

nmap --script ssh-auth-methods -p 22 192.168.1.15
```

## Findings

- SSH service detected on port 22.
- OpenSSH version identified.
- Supported SSH encryption algorithms enumerated.
- SSH host keys collected.
- Supported authentication methods identified.

## Learning Outcomes

- Learned how to detect SSH services.
- Learned how to identify SSH versions.
- Learned how to enumerate SSH algorithms.
- Learned how to retrieve SSH host keys.
- Learned how to identify supported authentication methods.

